---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Storage" description="RankMySEO storage options — SQLite, Postgres Drizzle, Prisma, Kysely.">
  <h1>Storage options</h1>
  <p class="lede">
    Default path: <code>createStore(url)</code> from <code>@rankmyseo/storage</code> (Drizzle).
    Optional packages implement the same <code>RankStore</code> contract for Prisma and Kysely.
  </p>

  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Option</th>
        <th>Package</th>
        <th>Factory</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>SQLite (Drizzle)</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/storage</code></td>
        <td><code>createStore("sqlite://…")</code> or <code>:memory:</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Postgres (Drizzle)</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/storage</code></td>
        <td><code>createStore("postgres://…")</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Postgres (Prisma)</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/storage-prisma</code></td>
        <td><code>createPrismaStore(url)</code></td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Postgres (Kysely)</td>
        <td><code>@rankmyseo/storage-kysely</code></td>
        <td><code>createKyselyStore(url)</code></td>
      </tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Migrations</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><code>npx rankmyseo migrate</code> runs inline DDL via <code>createStore()</code> (not <code>drizzle-kit migrate</code>).</li>
    <li>Prisma: prefer <code>prisma migrate</code> / <code>db push</code> with the schema shipped in <code>@rankmyseo/storage-prisma</code>.</li>
    <li>Contract tests: <code>runStoreContractTests</code> from <code>@rankmyseo/core/testing</code>. Postgres suites run when <code>RANKMYSEO_POSTGRES_URL</code> or <code>DATABASE_URL</code> is set.</li>
  </ul>

  <pre><code>import &#123; createStore &#125; from "@rankmyseo/storage";
// or: createPrismaStore / createKyselyStore from their packages

const store = createStore(process.env.DATABASE_URL!);</code></pre>
</BaseLayout>
